  "text": "The Kubernetes controller work queue with rate limiting is implemented in the staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/util/workqueue package within kubernetes/kubernetes. The core components are:\n\n**Base Queue Interface:**\n- `TypedInterface[T]` in queue.go defines the fundamental queue contract with Add(item T), Get() (item T, shutdown bool), and Done(item T) methods. The concrete implementation is `Typed[T]`.\n\n**Rate Limiting Interface:**\n- `TypedRateLimitingInterface[T]` in rate_limiting_queue.go extends TypedDelayingInterface with rate limiting capabilities including AddRateLimited(item T), Forget(item T), and NumRequeues(item T) methods. The concrete implementation is `rateLimitingType[T]`.\n\n**Rate Limiters:**\n- `TypedItemExponentialFailureRateLimiter[T]` in default_rate_limiters.go implements exponential backoff based on failure count, using baseDelay*2^<num-failures> formula.\n- `TypedBucketRateLimiter[T]` in default_rate_limiters.go implements token bucket rate limiting using golang.org/x/time/rate package.\n- `DefaultTypedControllerRateLimiter[T]()` in default_rate_limiters.go creates a composite rate limiter using NewTypedMaxOfRateLimiter that combines both ItemExponentialFailureRateLimiter and BucketRateLimiter.\n\n**Controller Reconcile Loop Pattern:**\nThe example in staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/examples/workqueue/main.go demonstrates the controller pattern:\n1. Create queue using NewTypedRateLimitingQueue with DefaultTypedControllerRateLimiter\n2. Add items to queue via informer event handlers using queue.Add(key)\n3. Worker loop calls queue.Get() to retrieve items\n4. Process item and call queue.Done(key) when complete\n5. On error, call queue.AddRateLimited(key) for retry with backoff\n6. Call queue.Forget(key) on success to clear retry history\n\nReal controller implementations like bootstrapsigner.go (pkg/controller/bootstrap/) and certificate_controller.go (pkg/controller/certificates/) follow this same pattern, creating the queue with NewTypedRateLimitingQueueWithConfig, and using Add() in event handlers, Get()/Done() in the worker loop, and AddRateLimited() for error handling.\n\nThe delaying_queue.go provides TypedDelayingInterface which is the base for rate-limiting queues, adding AddAfter(item T, duration) capability for delayed requeuing."
}

